rdf:Description.lla:note: Ship owner: Thomas Jones, Aberystwith. Voyage from Hull to Cette, in Europe and across the Atlantic. Includes Release list, signed by sailors leaving at Antwerp and receipt regarding discharging of 5 seamen and engaging of 5 further seamen. Logbook covers this voyage and the following voyage. Certificate no: 27716.

Owner: Thomas Jones, Aberystwith. Voyage from Antwerp to Runcorn. Entry compiled jointly from Agreement and Account of Crew for same voyage. File includes Release of Crew leaving on 13 Jan 1868. Logbook covers this voyage and the previous voyage. Certificate no: 27716.
There were several ships called Arica in the 1860s including those registered at Whitby, Aberystwyth, Dundee and Liverpool.
